  CC>    Hypertension F/U
  Comment>
  -  Limit salt intake: Reduce the amount of salt in your diet.
  -  Maintain a healthy weight: Aim for a balanced diet and exercise regularly to achieve and maintain a healthy weight.
  -  Moderate alcohol consumption: If you drink alcohol, do so in moderation.
  -  Eat potassium-rich foods: Include foods like bananas, oranges, spinach, tomatoes, and potatoes that are rich in potassium.
  -  Follow the DASH diet: Emphasize fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins, and low-fat dairy products in your diet.
  -  Consider specific needs: If you are black or an older adult, pay special attention to the effects of salt, potassium, and the DASH diet on blood pressure.
  -  Prevention and management: Dietary changes can help prevent hypertension in nonhypertensive individuals and complement drug therapy for those with high blood pressure.
